:::.col-12 .col-lg-6
### Cirrus Clouds{.text-center}
* Appearance: Thin, wispy, feather-like
* Altitude: High-level (above `6,000 m`)
* Weather Indication: Usually `signal fair weather` but can indicate an approaching `warm front or storm system`.
:::

:::.col-12 .col-lg-6
### Cumulus Clouds{.text-center}
* Appearance: Puffy, white, cotton-like with a flat base
* Altitude: Low to middle level (up to `2,000 m`)
* Weather Indication: ++Fair weather when isolated++, but large `cumulus` (cumulonimbus) can bring `thunderstorms`.

:::

:::.col-12
### Stratus Clouds{.text-center}
* Appearance: Gray, uniform, sheet-like covering the sky
* Altitude: Low-level (below `2,000 m`)
* Weather Indication: Often bring overcast `skies, drizzle, or light rain`.
:::


:::
